<head>PANT</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>BREATHE HEAVILY</item>
<item>BREATHE HARD</item>
<item>PUFF</item>
<item>HUFF AND PUFF</item>
<item>GASP</item>
<item>WHEEZE</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">喘</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BREATHE INTENSELY AND QUICKLY AFTER INTENSE MOVEMENT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>HUMAN BODY 5. 呼吸。</p>
<p>息，通稱。</p>
<p>喘，因勞累、炎熱、疾病等造成的急促呼吸。</p>
<p>嘽，專指由疲勞引起的急促呼吸。</p>
<p>哮，宋以後出現病名，指有聲響的急促呼吸。</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>喘息 is the standard modern word for panting.</p>
<p>氣短 refers to being short of breath.</p>
<p>氣急 refers to breathing hard.</p>
<p>氣促 refers to gasping for breath and breathing quickly.</p>
<p>氣咻咻 refers to huffing and puffing.</p>
<p>氣吁吁 refers to huffing and puffing.</p>
<p>氣喘吁吁 (prov) refers idiomatically to huffing and puffic.</p>
<p>上氣不接下氣 (prov) refers idiomatically and dramatically to huffing and puffic.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
